 {
  "uid": "doi:10.2139/ssrn.6704599",
  "drop": false,
  "field": "finance",
  "role": "method",
  "bullets": [
   "A review of the literature on interpretable machine learning and text-based large language models in finance, framed around regulatory explainability and portfolio decision transparency, with no sample, period, or geography.",
   "No model is run; the paper synthesizes prior interpretable machine learning models, large language model based financial text systems, and grounding architectures, and reports no validation against a ground truth.",
   "Concludes that explainability serves both regulatory compliance and portfolio transparency, and that progress depends on linking transparent predictive structure with grounded language based reasoning."
  ],
